---
To check:
git config --global user.name 
git config --global user.email 

To update:
git config --global user.name "REDELLESTIOKO"
git config --global user.email "redellestioko@rogers.com"


---
To check REMOTE Connected:
git remote -v

To ADD project
git remote add origin https://github.com/REDELLESTIOKO/helloworld-repo.git
or
git remote add origin https://github.com/REDELLESTIOKO/deployment_tracker.git
                      

To REMOVE the remote:
git remote remove origin

To verify that the repository running:
git status
\\If it says, “fatal: not a git repository,” that means you’ve successfully removed Git tracking.


///
---
---Summary of Key Commands
git init - Initialize a Git repository.

git add . - Stage all changes for commit.

git log - To check changes.

git commit -m "message" - Commit your changes with a message.

git push -u origin master - Push your code to the remote repository on GitHub.
